// drawing from a distribution that generates a type incompatible with the declared variable type
Integer x ~ Normal(mean=0.0, sd=1.0)
PositiveReal y ~ Normal(mean=0.0, sd=1.0)

// EXPECT AST
// (DR Integer x (CA Normal (AA mean 0.0) (AA sd 1.0)))
// (DR PositiveReal y (CA Normal (AA mean 0.0) (AA sd 1.0)))
// EXPECT AST

// EXPECT TYPE_ERRORS
// Expression of type `Real` cannot be assigned to variable `x` of type `Integer`. Change the type of the variable to `Distribution<Real>`, or change what value you draw and assign to it.
// Expression of type `Real` cannot be assigned to variable `y` of type `PositiveReal`. Change the type of the variable to `Distribution<Real>`, or change what value you draw and assign to it.
// EXPECT TYPE_ERRORS
